parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when it occurs on high-speed highways.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights appear on the dashboard
the engine stalls and will not restart
the vehicle may need to be towed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sulfur Dioxide Odor and Catalytic Converter Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of sulfur dioxide odor in the vehicle can cause discomfort and health concerns for occupants, and catalytic converter issues can lead to decreased engine performance and increased emissions.
symptoms: Strong sulfur dioxide odor emanating from the vents
potential issues with the catalytic converter.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission and Engine Control Unit (ECU) Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and ECU issues can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
multiple warning lights on the dashboard
potential need for transmission replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the lack of protection can cause occupants to suffer severe head trauma, broken limbs, and other debilitating injuries.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The theft of a license plate can lead to legal issues, fines, and potential identity theft if the stolen plate is used for illegal activities.
symptoms: License plate is missing
stolen
or removed from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Warning lights (triangle/exclamation mark and hybrid system warning light) appear on the dashboard
loss of power
inability to turn off the vehicle
vehicle behaves erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Battery and Wiring Issues)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents. In severe cases, it can also cause fires, as seen in the first complaint.
symptoms: The vehicle's engine turns off and on repeatedly
the engine idles hard
smoke comes from the engine
wires from the battery to the front of the car are damaged
the fan remains on even when the car is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and loss of power can cause the vehicle to lose speed and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle's speed decreases suddenly
the vehicle loses power
all indicator lights stay on
the vehicle drives normally after restarting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the tire failure occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: Tires show signs of splitting or cracking on the sidewall
tires lose air pressure
tires exhibit uneven wear
loud noise while driving
visible damage to the tire core.
